article.headline: Vanderbilt 83, Tennessee Tech 63
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. -- A.J. Ogilvy had 20 points, six rebounds and three assists as Vanderbilt defeated Tennessee Tech 83-63 on Saturday. Ogilvy made six of 10 field goals and shot 8 for 8 from the free throw line, as he reached 20 points for the second straight game. Jeffery Taylor had 14 points and seven rebounds for the Commodores (8-3), and freshman Lance Goulbourne added seven points and seven rebounds in 15 minutes off the bench. Frank Davis made four 3-pointers and led Tennessee Tech (6-4) with 19 points. His 3-pointer with 14:27 to play in the first half gave the Golden Eagles their last lead, 9-8. Daniel Northern added 14 points and grabbed 18 rebounds. He got Tech within three, 28-25, with a jumpshot with 5:10 remaining in the first half, but Vanderbilt responded with a 12-4 run.
